<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=13052&amp;p=151655#p151655"><![CDATA[
You need to use color palettes on the GBC. The GBC will completely ignore the BGP register for its palette. It has specificc registers for color. You may need to mess around with VRAM banks to get the BG showing up.<br /><br />See this page about video display stuff on the GBC: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://gbdev.gg8.se/wiki/articles/Video_Display">http://gbdev.gg8.se/wiki/articles/Video_Display</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6368">Shonumi</a> — Sun Jul 26, 2015 4:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
